[{"slug":"alternative-facts","title":"Alternative facts","date":1497275619050,"synopsis":"\"Alternative facts\" is a phrase used by U.S. Counselor to the President Kellyanne Conway during a Meet the Press interview on January 22, 2017, in which she defended White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer's false statement about the attendance numbers of Donald Trump's inauguration as President of the United States."},{"slug":"argument-from-ignorance","title":"Argument from ignorance","date":1512664556287,"synopsis":"Argument from ignorance (from Latin: argumentum ad ignorantiam), also known as appeal to ignorance (in which ignorance represents \"a lack of contrary evidence\"), is a fallacy in informal logic. It asserts that a proposition is true because it has not yet been proven false or a proposition is false because it has not yet been proven true."},{"slug":"argument-map","title":"Argument map","date":1497091666551,"synopsis":"In informal logic and philosophy, an argument map or argument diagram is a visual representation of the structure of an argument - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Argument_map wikipedia]"},{"slug":"baloney-detection-kit","title":"Baloney Detection Kit","date":1512665213909,"synopsis":"The [[Baloney Detection Kit]] is a set of tools for skeptical thinking that [[Karl Sagan]] lays out in his book [[The Demon-Haunted World]]. It's a [[Bullshit Detector]]."},{"slug":"bullshido","title":"Bullshido","date":1494361728772,"synopsis":"Bullshido is the art of fighting bullshit. Now more than ever we need this. We deserve it to ourselves and our own sense of self-respect, to stand up for the good stuff, the real stuff, and show zero tolerance to BS."},{"slug":"bullshido-academy","title":"Bullshido Academy","date":1494435019119,"synopsis":"So how do we do this? How do we train BS spotters? We ain't no use if we turn into simple [[Troll]]s. We need discipline. We need a method."},{"slug":"bullshit","title":"Bullshit","date":1512659854783,"synopsis":"This is a technical term. It is short for [[Bad Science]]."},{"slug":"changes-to-this-site","title":"Changes to this Site","date":1434641767059,"synopsis":"Below we list recent changes to this site only without also listing changes from the [[Neighbourhood]]:"},{"slug":"currently-working-on","title":"Currently Working On","date":1501361298013,"synopsis":"Here is a list of [[Recent Changes]] I consider important. View our experiments on the [[Scratch]] page. To clear stuff saved in your browser try [[Local Changes]]."},{"slug":"definition-of-bullshit","title":"Definition of Bullshit","date":1497274554529,"synopsis":"We are proposing creating a definition through exploring two directions: first though exploring examples, and deriving a definition based on case-law, or family relationships."},{"slug":"double-standards","title":"Double Standards","date":1514027468806,"synopsis":"https://www.podtrac.com/pts/redirect.mp3/audio.wnyc.org/otm/otm122217_cms821636_pod.mp3#t=45:22,52:37"},{"slug":"doubt","title":"Doubt","date":1500997476808,"synopsis":"Doubt characterises a status in which the mind remains suspended between two contradictory propositions and unable to assent to either of them. Doubt on an emotional level is indecision between belief and disbelief. Doubt involves uncertainty, distrust or lack of sureness of an alleged fact, an action, a motive, or a decision. Doubt questions a notion of a perceived \"reality\", and may involve delaying or rejecting relevant action out of concerns for mistakes or faults or appropriateness. (Compare paradox) - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Doubt wikipedia]"},{"slug":"examples-of-bullshit","title":"Examples of Bullshit","date":1498483679780,"synopsis":"The aim here is to collect examples of [[BS]]. These can be used to inform the design of the [[Bullshit Detector]], and also to be used as a basis for training algorithms and black belts."},{"slug":"factoid","title":"Factoid","date":1492332468429,"synopsis":"In thinking about [[Fake news]], the word arrived in my consciousness through a merger of [[Fact]] and [[Plantoid]]. For me it represented the weaponisation of [[Meme]]s for political purposes."},{"slug":"fake-news","title":"Fake news","date":1492256245271,"synopsis":"Fake news is a type of hoax or deliberate spread of misinformation (false information), be it via the traditional print or broadcasting news media or via Internet-based social media."},{"slug":"fedwiki-tools","title":"Fedwiki Tools","date":1511705109115,"synopsis":"Here we list a few tools that are of particular use in managing and creating [[Fedwiki]] content. Check [[Recycled pages]] to find delted pages."},{"slug":"fire-with-fire","title":"Fire With Fire","date":1514025774410,"synopsis":"When it comes to fighting fire with fire, common knowledge would have us leave the pyrotechnics to the trained professionals."},{"slug":"fraudulent-mindset","title":"Fraudulent Mindset","date":1419410380000,"synopsis":"These \"attacking\" titles (\"fraudulent\") need to go. It is not helpful. I suggest something like \"[[Integrity And Safety Versus Nimbleness And Dynamism]]\".  I'm leaning toward <b>[[Purity Versus Organic]]</b>."},{"slug":"future-law","title":"Future Law","date":1497091447826,"synopsis":"Future law is law - but not as you know it Jim. It is a pragmatic system, or [[Legal Hack]] that we are able to compose partly out of code, and partly out of real-world legal elements."},{"slug":"harry-frankfurt","title":"Harry Frankfurt","date":1497717752882,"synopsis":"Harry Gordon Frankfurt (born May 29, 1929) is an American philosopher. He is professor emeritus of philosophy at Princeton University, where he taught from 1990 until 2002, and previously taught at Yale University, Rockefeller University, and Ohio State University - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harry_Frankfurt wikipedia]"},{"slug":"he-will-not-divide-us","title":"He Will Not Divide Us","date":1502699234905,"synopsis":"HEWILLNOTDIVIDE.US is an ongoing durational artwork by LaBeouf, Rönkkö & Turner - [http://www.hewillnotdivide.us/ hewillnotdivide.us]"},{"slug":"karl-popper","title":"Karl Popper","date":1469276327353,"synopsis":"Sir Karl Raimund Popper CH FBA FRS (28 July 1902 – 17 September 1994) was an Austrian-British philosopher and professor. He is generally regarded as one of the greatest philosophers of science of the 20th century - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karl_Popper wikipedia]"},{"slug":"lyrebirdai","title":"Lyrebird.ai","date":1514374674787,"synopsis":"As pioneers of this technology, we believe that we have the responsibility to guide its launch to developers and the general public. We have worked hard to create principles that accurately reflect the values we espouse as technologists. We have sought the insights of machine learning researchers, our investors, ethics professors, and many others."},{"slug":"mr-hollowell-didnt-like-that","title":"Mr. Hollowell Didn’t Like That","date":1501833506274,"synopsis":"Arrested, arraigned, indicted, tried, convicted, and sentenced to die in the electric chair in 24 hours."},{"slug":"new-age-bullshit-generator","title":"New Age Bullshit Generator","date":1501361362928,"synopsis":"So, what is this for? Put it on your website as placeholder text. Print it out as a speech for your yoga class and see if anyone can guess a computer wrote it. Use it to write the hottest new bestseller in the self-help section, or give false hope to depressed friends and family members - [http://sebpearce.com/bullshit/ sebpearce.com]"},{"slug":"on-bullshit","title":"On Bullshit","date":1497717810078,"synopsis":"\"On Bullshit\" (2005), by philosopher Harry G. Frankfurt, is an essay that presents a theory of bullshit that defines the concept and analyzes the applications of bullshit in the contexts of communication. Frankfurt determines that bullshit is speech intended to persuade (a.k.a. rhetoric), without regard for truth. The liar cares about the truth and attempts to hide it; the bullshitter doesn't care if what they say is true or false, but rather only cares whether or not their listener is persuaded - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/On_Bullshit wikipedia]"},{"slug":"pepe-the-frog","title":"Pepe the Frog","date":1502699818314,"synopsis":"Pepe the Frog  is a popular Internet meme. The green anthropomorphic frog with a frog-like face and a humanoid body is originally from a comic series by Matt Furie called Boy's Club. It became an Internet meme when its popularity steadily grew across Myspace, Gaia Online and 4chan in 2008. By 2015, it had become one of the most popular memes used on 4chan - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pepe_the_Frog wikipedia]"},{"slug":"philosophy-unbound","title":"Philosophy Unbound","date":1515069318490,"synopsis":"Sehr geehrte Forschungsgemeinde, liebe Bullshitologinnen und Bullshitologen, wir laden zum ersten internationalen Bullshitologiekongress! / Dear scientific community, most honoured fellow..- [http://philosophyunbound.tumblr.com/post/161886866992/philosophy-unbound-17-bullshit tumblr.com]"},{"slug":"putin-on-foreign-policy","title":"Putin on Foreign Policy","date":1497181855031,"synopsis":"Here we look at some of Putin's statements and how he communicates politically. There is some interesting forms of [[BS]], and [[Propaganda]] to be derived from his TV appearances?"},{"slug":"ring-of-truth","title":"Ring of Truth","date":1508770204070,"synopsis":"Most people won't write unless they've had a good experience. This makes for a selection bias in writing on methods. Rather we look for hard-won experience with enough hard that we see ourselves in it."},{"slug":"science-wars","title":"Science wars","date":1509639595793,"synopsis":"The science wars were a series of intellectual exchanges, between scientific realists and postmodernist critics, about the nature of scientific theory and intellectual inquiry. They took place principally in the United States in the 1990s in the academic and mainstream press. Scientific realists (such as Norman Levitt, Paul R. Gross, Jean Bricmont and Alan Sokal) argued that scientific knowledge is real, and accused the postmodernists of having effectively rejected scientific objectivity, the scientific method, Empiricism, and scientific knowledge. Postm"},{"slug":"techniques-of-bullshit","title":"Techniques of Bullshit","date":1497103878695,"synopsis":"Techniques of:"},{"slug":"techno-legal-architecture","title":"Techno-legal Architecture","date":1497100884498,"synopsis":"This is the term I use for an amalgamation or synthesis of law, code and organisation apparatus."},{"slug":"the-demon-haunted-world","title":"The Demon-Haunted World","date":1512658876410,"synopsis":"The Demon-Haunted World: Science as a Candle in the Dark is a 1995 book by astrophysicist Carl Sagan, in which the author aims to explain the scientific method to laypeople, and to encourage people to learn critical and skeptical thinking."},{"slug":"the-policemans-beard-is-half-constructed","title":"The Policeman's Beard is Half Constructed","date":1498483657275,"synopsis":"The Policeman's Beard is Half Constructed is the first book written by a computer. See also companies like [[Narrative Science]]."},{"slug":"trumps-inauguration-in-2017","title":"Trump's inauguration in 2017","date":1497275328170,"synopsis":"Here is the classic [[Fake News]] and [[Alternative Facts]] case of Donald Trumps inauguration:"},{"slug":"truth","title":"Truth","date":1509637898976,"synopsis":"Truth is most often used to mean being in accord with fact or reality, or fidelity to an original or standard. Truth may also often be used in modern contexts to refer to an idea of \"truth to self,\" or authenticity - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Truth wikipedia]"},{"slug":"truth-in-code","title":"Truth in Code","date":1439107012504,"synopsis":"/bin/true is a script which just returns true so you can do something like - [http://www.quora.com/What-is-the-dumbest-code-ever-made-that-has-become-famous quora.com]"},{"slug":"truth-warriors","title":"Truth Warriors","date":1501834521069,"synopsis":"A great podcast about truth and the obsession to uncover it. The stories of a few folks ready to fight the future of fakery - [http://www.radiolab.org/story/truth-warriors/?utm_source=sharedUrl&utm_medium=metatag&utm_campaign=sharedUrl radiolab.org]"},{"slug":"welcome-visitors","title":"Welcome Visitors","date":1515068721399,"synopsis":"[[Bullshido]] is the art of fighting [[bullshit]]. We believe there is too much [[BS]] in this world and we are dedicated to finding ways to reduce it."},{"slug":"whats-left-when-youre-right","title":"What's Left When You're Right?","date":1471597082876,"synopsis":"From the stage to the cage, a series of showdowns that leave us wondering about the price of being right ... or coming from the left - [http://www.radiolab.org/story/whats-left-when-youre-right/?utm_source=sharedUrl&utm_medium=metatag&utm_campaign=sharedUrl radiolab.org]"},{"slug":"who-pays-the-piper","title":"Who pays the Piper?","date":1514026781828,"synopsis":"[[Who pays the Piper?]]. Does it make a significant difference where news is funded from? What is the difference between local government funding for news, and a single rich proprietor?"},{"slug":"wiki-truth","title":"Wiki Truth","date":1416076483240,"synopsis":"While many people question the truth of what they read in wiki, I question their understanding of truth itself."},{"slug":"zara-shop-art-theft","title":"Zara Shop Art Theft","date":1498483309513,"synopsis":"Once is a mistake. This many times is inexcusable."}]